PRD — Mini Library Management System
1. The library holds Books. Some can be borrowed; some reference items stay in.
2. Users: Members (borrow/return) and Librarians (manage catalog).
3. Every user has a unique ID. Track total users.
4. Books have sub-types: Textbook, Novel.
5. A Loan tracks who borrowed what. Members have a borrow limit.
6. You must be able to SEARCH the catalog and LOOP OVER the library.


